Rake task to request full partner records from SCSB API
Override an existing xml file in /data/marc_liberation_files/scsb_update_files while processing Full scsb files
Zip::DestinationFileExistsError in Full Partner Recap Records

comments.body:
Looking through the code, Full files that are imported through SCSB are https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/55d3495c1bf4e26c8c2759dd921940e7d41f0871/app/models/scsb/partner_updates.rb#L48 processed and extracted in the `data/marc_liberation_files/partner_update_scratch` directory. The error that was generated was because the file existed and raised an error. We should override it in this case and have this error fail the process. I will open an issue for this. 
I confirmed with @hackartisan who has also seen the same error in the past. For now we deleted the files in `data/marc_liberation_files/partner_update_scratch` and deleted the unfinished `Full partner Recap Records` job so that is not stale in the events page. 
The 2 extra events for 'Full partner Recap Records' were created because while the Scsb import job was still running in sidekiq we deployed twice in production (@hackartisan thanks for the observation). Unfortunately that causes sidekiq to restart.

figgy.title: CSV-migrated item-level metadata for scanned resources from Historic Postcards Finding Aid Collection is not displaying in DPUL Collection.

comments.body:
This should be a figgy ticket, so I'll transfer it there.

I'm not really sure what to do here. I'm tempted to convert these to simple resources, which should make the JSON-LD display (and thus sync over more metadata), but that'll make it so you can't edit the record as well. Alternatively we could make local values display for scanned resources, but there's no way in the app to actually fill those values in.
I have no problem converting all items in this collection to simple resources and not having the ability to edit the record. @escowles , do you concur?
Yes, converting to SimpleResources seems fine to me  this is legacy PUDL content that won't be actively edited.
